import matplotlib
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import platform

#    
path = "c:/Windows/Fonts/malgun.ttf"
from matplotlib import font_manager, rc
if platform.system() == 'Darwin':
    rc('font', family='AppleGothic')
elif platform.system() == 'Windows':
    font_name = font_manager.FontProperties(fname=path).get_name()
    font = {'weight' : 'bold','size': 22}
    rc('font', family=font_name, **font)
else:
    print('Unknown system')

# !
Target_keyword = ''
this_month = '2016'
# plot   title   
title_lc = Target_keyword + '_++_  _'+this_month
title_wc = Target_keyword + '_++_ WordCloud_'+this_month
#    export  directory    
fig_name_lc = '../'+Target_keyword+'__'+this_month
fig_name_wwc = '../'+Target_keyword+'_w_'+this_month
fig_name_bwc = '../'+Target_keyword+'_b_'+this_month

#   xlsx . 
file_name = '../KBS/DaumPoli/new_freq/_2016_new.xlsx'
freq_df = pd.read_excel(file_name)

#   
print(' : ',len(freq_df))

#   del_words +     del_words 
current_del_words = del_words.copy()
More_del_words = ['']
current_del_words.extend(More_del_words)
print('   : ',len(current_del_words))

del_index = [i for i in range(len(freq_df)) if freq_df['words'][i] in current_del_words]
freq_df.drop(del_index, inplace = True)
freq_df.reset_index(inplace = True, drop = True)
print('    : ',len(freq_df))

#    corpus  !!
corpus = []
for i in range(len(freq_df)):
    corpus.extend([str(freq_df['words'][i])]*freq_df['freq'][i])
whole_tokens_text = nltk.Text(corpus)

#     #   
#     count_list = freq_df.values.tolist()
#     freq_dict = dict(count_list)

###    : 50! 
matplotlib.rcParams.update({'font.size': 11,'font.weight' : 'bold'})
pylab.show = lambda: pylab.savefig(fig_name_lc+'.png',dpi=400)
plt.figure(figsize=(15,6))
plt.title(title_lc)
whole_tokens_text.plot()
plt.show()


###  ! 
#  200  !
wordcloud = WordCloud(
    font_path="c:/Windows/Fonts/malgun.ttf", 
    relative_scaling = 0.2, 
    #background_color = 'white',
    width = 1200, height = 600
).generate_from_frequencies(dict(whole_tokens_text.vocab().most_common(200)))

plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.title(title_wc)
plt.imshow(wordcloud)
plt.axis("off")
pyplot.savefig(fig_name_bwc+'.png', dpi=400)
plt.show()

wordcloud = WordCloud(
    font_path="c:/Windows/Fonts/malgun.ttf", 
    relative_scaling = 0.2, 
    background_color = 'white',
    width = 1200, height = 600
).generate_from_frequencies(dict(whole_tokens_text.vocab().most_common(200)))

plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
